title: Two people make lucky escape after plane crashes in rural Victoria - 9news.com.au
text:
Two people make lucky escape after plane crashes in rural Victoria By 9NEWS The two people aboard the light plane made it out uninjured after it crashed. (9NEWS) 
Two people on board a light plane made a lucky escape after the aircraft crashed into a paddock near a Victorian airport this afternoon. 
Authorities say the crash occurred near Latrobe Regional Airport in Traralgon about 1.25pm today. 
Paramedics say the man and woman who were on board the plane were shaken, but not injured. 
There is no word on what caused the plane to crash. 
Authorities are at the scene investigating. Â© Nine Digital Pty Ltd 2017
